      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Not required at MRL 2; equivalency addressed through test conditions factor.",
      "rationale": "Equivalency of input parameters between the validation experiment and the COU is addressed implicitly through the test conditions and relevance factors assessed above. A separate equivalency assessment is not required at MRL 2."
    }
  ],
  "hasWeakener": [],
  "hasDecisionRecord": {
    "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/decision/morrison-cou1-cpb-decision-2026",
    "type": "DecisionRecord",
    "actor": "https://uofa.net/synth/actor/morrison-cfd-credibility-team",
    "role": "Credibility assessment team",
    "outcome": "Accepted",
    "rationale": "Following comprehensive screening of all 13 ASME V&V 40 credibility factors at Model Risk Level 2, the credibility assessment team concludes that the CFD hemolysis model is acceptable for the CPB COU. All seven assessed factors meet or exceed their required credibility levels, and the six factors not assessed are appropriately scoped out under MRL 2 provisions. Critically, throughout the entire assessment process — spanning software qualification, numerical verification, mesh refinement, validation comparison, and operational deployment across three prior pump studies — no failure modes have been observed in the modelling workflow, no contraindications have been reported by any analyst or reviewer, and we have not encountered any issues that would call into question the reliability of the hemolysis predictions. The absence of any identified deficiency across the full assessment record, combined with the satisfactory quantitative outcomes on assessed factors, provides the basis for accepting the model for regulatory submission. The relative hemolysis index RH < 1 criterion is met at all five operating points, and the model is approved for use in identifying worst-case hemolysis conditions for the Class II CPB device.",
    "decidedAt": "2026-04-19T00:00:00Z"
  },
